(NULL, 'Kartika Purnima is an important festival in Odisha. What is it primarily associated with?', 'Harvest celebration', 'Boat racing in Chilika Lake', 'Temple visits and lighting lamps', 'New Year celebration', 'C', 1, 'Festivals', 'medium', '["Kartika Purnima", "Festivals", "Chilika"]'::jsonb, 'Kartika Purnima is celebrated with great devotion, involving temple visits, lighting lamps, and taking holy dips. It also marks the beginning of the boating season in Chilika Lake.'),
(NULL, 'During Rath Yatra, the three chariots of Jagannath, Balabhadra, and Subhadra are pulled to which temple?', 'Gundicha Temple', 'Lingaraj Temple', 'Mukteswar Temple', 'Konark Temple', 'A', 1, 'Festivals', 'medium', '["Rath Yatra", "Jagannath", "Gundicha Temple", "Puri"]'::jsonb, 'During Rath Yatra, the deities are taken from Jagannath Temple to Gundicha Temple, where they stay for 7 days before returning.'),
(NULL, 'What is the traditional name for the return journey of Rath Yatra when the deities come back to the main temple?', 'Bahuda Yatra', 'Snana Yatra', 'Chandan Yatra', 'Nabakalebara', 'A', 1, 'Festivals', 'hard', '["Rath Yatra", "Bahuda Yatra", "Jagannath", "Festivals"]'::jsonb, 'Bahuda Yatra is the return journey of the deities from Gundicha Temple back to the Jagannath Temple after their 7-day stay.'),
(NULL, 'Nuakhai is celebrated with the offering of the first grain of the season. What grain is traditionally offered?', 'Rice', 'Wheat', 'Millet', 'Corn', 'A', 1, 'Festivals', 'easy', '["Nuakhai", "Harvest Festival", "Rice", "Western Odisha"]'::jsonb, 'Nuakhai is a harvest festival where the first grain of rice from the new harvest is offered to the goddess, followed by family celebrations.'),
(NULL, 'Raja Parba is a unique three-day festival. On which day do women and girls celebrate by not doing household work?', 'First day (Pahili Raja)', 'Second day (Raja Sankranti)', 'Third day (Basi Raja)', 'All three days', 'D', 1, 'Festivals', 'medium', '["Raja Parba", "Women Festival", "Fertility Festival"]'::jsonb, 'During all three days of Raja Parba, women and girls take a break from household work, wear new clothes, apply alta (red dye) on their feet, and enjoy swings.'),
(NULL, 'Snana Yatra is a festival where the deities are given a ceremonial bath. In which month does it occur?', 'Jyestha (May-June)', 'Ashadha (June-July)', 'Shravana (July-August)', 'Bhadraba (August-September)', 'A', 1, 'Festivals', 'hard', '["Snana Yatra", "Jagannath", "Festivals", "Puri"]'::jsonb, 'Snana Yatra occurs on the full moon day of Jyestha month, where the deities are given a ceremonial bath with 108 pots of water.'),
(NULL, 'Chandan Yatra is a 42-day festival in Puri. What is it primarily known for?', 'Sandalwood paste application', 'Boat festival in Narendra Tank', 'Flower decoration', 'Music and dance performances', 'B', 1, 'Festivals', 'hard', '["Chandan Yatra", "Jagannath", "Narendra Tank", "Festivals"]'::jsonb, 'Chandan Yatra is a 42-day festival where the deities are taken in boats to the Narendra Tank for a boat festival, along with application of sandalwood paste.'),
(NULL, 'Which festival in Odisha marks the beginning of the agricultural year and is celebrated with great enthusiasm in rural areas?', 'Nuakhai', 'Raja Parba', 'Makar Sankranti', 'Pana Sankranti', 'D', 1, 'Festivals', 'medium', '["Pana Sankranti", "New Year", "Festivals", "Odisha"]'::jsonb, 'Pana Sankranti (Maha Vishuva Sankranti) marks the Odia New Year and the beginning of the agricultural season, celebrated with pana (a sweet drink) and various rituals.'),

