(NULL, 'In which year was Odia recognized as a classical language by the Government of India?', '2012', '2013', '2014', '2015', 'C', 1, 'Language & Literature', 'medium', '["Odia Language", "Classical Language", "Literature"]'::jsonb, 'Odia was recognized as the 6th classical language of India in 2014, joining Sanskrit, Tamil, Telugu, Kannada, and Malayalam.'),
(NULL, 'Who wrote the famous Odia epic "Mahabharata" in Odia language, making it accessible to common people?', 'Sarala Das', 'Jagannath Das', 'Balaram Das', 'Achyutananda Das', 'A', 1, 'Language & Literature', 'medium', '["Sarala Das", "Mahabharata", "Epic", "Literature"]'::jsonb, 'Sarala Das, a 15th-century poet, translated and adapted the Mahabharata into Odia, making it the first major literary work in the language.'),
(NULL, 'Which famous Odia poet is known as "Kabi Samrat" (Emperor of Poets) and wrote in the kavya style?', 'Upendra Bhanja', 'Radhanath Ray', 'Fakir Mohan Senapati', 'Gangadhar Meher', 'A', 1, 'Language & Literature', 'medium', '["Upendra Bhanja", "Kabi Samrat", "Poetry", "Literature"]'::jsonb, 'Upendra Bhanja (1670-1720) is known as "Kabi Samrat" and is famous for his kavya poetry, particularly "Baidehisha Bilasa" and "Lavanyabati".'),
(NULL, 'Who is considered the father of modern Odia prose and wrote the famous novel "Chha Mana Atha Guntha"?', 'Fakir Mohan Senapati', 'Radhanath Ray', 'Madhusudan Das', 'Gopabandhu Das', 'A', 1, 'Language & Literature', 'easy', '["Fakir Mohan Senapati", "Modern Prose", "Chha Mana Atha Guntha", "Literature"]'::jsonb, 'Fakir Mohan Senapati (1843-1918) is considered the father of modern Odia prose. His novel "Chha Mana Atha Guntha" (Six Acres and a Third) is a masterpiece of Indian literature.'),
(NULL, 'Which Odia poet is known for his work "Chilika" and is considered one of the pioneers of modern Odia poetry?', 'Radhanath Ray', 'Upendra Bhanja', 'Gangadhar Meher', 'Madhusudan Rao', 'A', 1, 'Language & Literature', 'hard', '["Radhanath Ray", "Chilika", "Modern Poetry", "Literature"]'::jsonb, 'Radhanath Ray (1848-1908) is known for his poem "Chilika", which describes the beauty of Chilika Lake. He is considered a pioneer of modern Odia poetry.'),
(NULL, 'The Odia Ramayana was translated by which famous poet, making it one of the earliest translations?', 'Balaram Das', 'Jagannath Das', 'Sarala Das', 'Achyutananda Das', 'B', 1, 'Language & Literature', 'hard', '["Jagannath Das", "Ramayana", "Translation", "Literature"]'::jsonb, 'Jagannath Das (1490-1550) translated the Ramayana into Odia, creating "Jagannath Das''s Ramayana", which is widely read and respected.'),
(NULL, 'Which Odia writer is known for his social reform works and was a key figure in the Odia language movement?', 'Gopabandhu Das', 'Madhusudan Das', 'Fakir Mohan Senapati', 'Radhanath Ray', 'A', 1, 'Language & Literature', 'medium', '["Gopabandhu Das", "Social Reform", "Literature", "Freedom Fighter"]'::jsonb, 'Gopabandhu Das (1877-1928) was a social reformer, freedom fighter, and writer who played a crucial role in the Odia language movement and social reforms.'),
(NULL, 'Who wrote the famous Odia novel "Basanti" and is considered one of the early modern Odia novelists?', 'Kalindi Charan Panigrahi', 'Gopinath Mohanty', 'Fakir Mohan Senapati', 'Manoranjan Das', 'A', 1, 'Language & Literature', 'hard', '["Kalindi Charan Panigrahi", "Basanti", "Novel", "Literature"]'::jsonb, 'Kalindi Charan Panigrahi (1901-1991) wrote "Basanti" and other novels, contributing significantly to modern Odia literature.'),

