(NULL, 'Odissi dance is one of the eight classical dance forms of India. How many basic poses or "bhangas" are there in Odissi?', 'Three bhangas', 'Four bhangas', 'Five bhangas', 'Six bhangas', 'A', 1, 'Traditional Arts', 'hard', '["Odissi Dance", "Bhangas", "Classical Dance"]'::jsonb, 'Odissi dance has three basic bhangas (poses): Abhanga (slight bend), Tribhanga (triple bend), and Atibhanga (extreme bend).'),
(NULL, 'Pattachitra paintings traditionally depict stories from which epic?', 'Ramayana', 'Mahabharata', 'Both Ramayana and Mahabharata', 'Puranas and religious stories', 'D', 1, 'Traditional Arts', 'medium', '["Pattachitra", "Traditional Art", "Painting", "Odisha"]'::jsonb, 'Pattachitra paintings traditionally depict stories from Puranas, religious texts, and mythological stories, often featuring Jagannath, Krishna, and other deities.'),
(NULL, 'Gotipua dance is performed by young boys. What does "Gotipua" mean in Odia?', 'Young dancer', 'Single boy', 'Boy dressed as girl', 'Little performer', 'B', 1, 'Traditional Arts', 'medium', '["Gotipua", "Dance", "Traditional", "Odisha"]'::jsonb, 'Gotipua means "single boy" in Odia. These young boys dress as girls and perform acrobatic dance, which is considered a precursor to modern Odissi dance.'),
(NULL, 'Which traditional Odia art form involves creating intricate designs by cutting and pasting colored cloth pieces?', 'Pattachitra', 'Applique work', 'Silver filigree', 'Stone carving', 'B', 1, 'Traditional Arts', 'medium', '["Applique", "Handicraft", "Traditional Art", "Pipili"]'::jsonb, 'Applique work, particularly famous in Pipili, involves cutting and stitching colored cloth pieces to create beautiful designs, often used for umbrellas, canopies, and wall hangings.'),
(NULL, 'Sambalpuri dance is a folk dance form. Which region of Odisha is it primarily associated with?', 'Coastal Odisha', 'Western Odisha', 'Northern Odisha', 'Southern Odisha', 'B', 1, 'Traditional Arts', 'easy', '["Sambalpuri Dance", "Folk Dance", "Western Odisha"]'::jsonb, 'Sambalpuri dance is a vibrant folk dance form from Western Odisha, particularly from the Sambalpur region, performed during festivals and celebrations.'),
(NULL, 'Which traditional art form of Odisha involves creating beautiful designs on palm leaves using a stylus?', 'Pattachitra', 'Talapatra Chitra', 'Stone carving', 'Wood carving', 'B', 1, 'Traditional Arts', 'medium', '["Talapatra Chitra", "Palm Leaf", "Traditional Art"]'::jsonb, 'Talapatra Chitra involves engraving intricate designs and texts on palm leaves using a stylus, a traditional art form that has been practiced in Odisha for centuries.'),
(NULL, 'The traditional "Danda Nacha" is performed during which festival?', 'Durga Puja', 'Nuakhai', 'Raja Parba', 'Dussehra', 'D', 1, 'Traditional Arts', 'hard', '["Danda Nacha", "Folk Dance", "Dussehra", "Western Odisha"]'::jsonb, 'Danda Nacha is a traditional folk dance performed during Dussehra in Western Odisha, where performers dance with sticks (danda) in a rhythmic pattern.'),
(NULL, 'Which classical dance form of Odisha is known for its graceful movements and expressions, often depicting stories of Radha and Krishna?', 'Odissi', 'Gotipua', 'Chhau', 'Sambalpuri', 'A', 1, 'Traditional Arts', 'easy', '["Odissi Dance", "Classical Dance", "Radha Krishna"]'::jsonb, 'Odissi is the classical dance form of Odisha, known for its graceful movements, intricate footwork, and expressive storytelling, often depicting stories of Radha and Krishna.'),

