(NULL, 'Rasgulla, one of the most famous Odia sweets, is traditionally made from which ingredient?', 'Chhena (cottage cheese)', 'Khoya (milk solids)', 'Besan (gram flour)', 'Semolina', 'A', 1, 'Food & Cuisine', 'easy', '["Rasgulla", "Sweet", "Chhena", "Cuisine"]'::jsonb, 'Rasgulla is made from chhena (cottage cheese) and soaked in sugar syrup. It originated in Odisha and is now popular throughout India.'),
(NULL, 'Chhena Poda is a famous dessert from Odisha. What does "Poda" mean in Odia?', 'Sweet', 'Burnt', 'Soft', 'Fried', 'B', 1, 'Food & Cuisine', 'medium', '["Chhena Poda", "Dessert", "Cuisine", "Odisha"]'::jsonb, 'Chhena Poda means "burnt cheese" in Odia. It is a caramelized cheese dessert that is baked until it gets a brown, burnt appearance on top.'),
(NULL, 'Pakhala is a traditional Odia dish, especially popular during summer. How is it typically served?', 'Hot with vegetables', 'Cold with curd and spices', 'Fried with onions', 'Steamed with dal', 'B', 1, 'Food & Cuisine', 'easy', '["Pakhala", "Traditional Food", "Summer Dish", "Cuisine"]'::jsonb, 'Pakhala is fermented rice soaked in water, typically served cold with curd, green chilies, and sometimes with fried fish or vegetables.'),
(NULL, 'Dahibara Aloodum is a popular street food. In which city is it most famous?', 'Bhubaneswar', 'Cuttack', 'Puri', 'Rourkela', 'B', 1, 'Food & Cuisine', 'medium', '["Dahibara Aloodum", "Street Food", "Cuttack", "Cuisine"]'::jsonb, 'Dahibara Aloodum is a very popular street food in Cuttack, consisting of deep-fried lentil dumplings (dahibara) served with curd and spiced potato curry (aloodum).'),
(NULL, 'Which traditional Odia sweet is made by deep-frying chhena balls and soaking them in sugar syrup?', 'Rasgulla', 'Rasmalai', 'Chhena Gaja', 'Kheer', 'C', 1, 'Food & Cuisine', 'hard', '["Chhena Gaja", "Sweet", "Cuisine", "Odisha"]'::jsonb, 'Chhena Gaja is made by shaping chhena into rectangular pieces, deep-frying them, and then soaking in sugar syrup. It has a unique texture and taste.'),

