(NULL, 'Jhoti Chita is a traditional floor art form. What material is traditionally used to draw Jhoti?', 'Colored powder', 'Rice paste', 'Turmeric paste', 'Chalk powder', 'B', 1, 'Culture & Traditions', 'medium', '["Jhoti Chita", "Floor Art", "Rangoli", "Traditions"]'::jsonb, 'Jhoti Chita is drawn using rice paste (pithau) mixed with water. It is a traditional floor art form, similar to Rangoli, used during festivals and auspicious occasions.'),
(NULL, 'Sambalpuri saree is a famous traditional attire. Which district is it primarily associated with?', 'Sambalpur', 'Bargarh', 'Sonepur', 'Balangir', 'B', 1, 'Culture & Traditions', 'medium', '["Sambalpuri Saree", "Traditional Attire", "Bargarh", "Handloom"]'::jsonb, 'Sambalpuri saree, known for its ikat (bandha) work, is primarily associated with Bargarh district, though it is also made in Sambalpur and other Western Odisha districts.'),
(NULL, 'The traditional "Mardala" is a percussion instrument. What type of instrument is it?', 'String instrument', 'Wind instrument', 'Percussion instrument (drum)', 'Brass instrument', 'C', 1, 'Culture & Traditions', 'medium', '["Mardala", "Musical Instrument", "Percussion", "Odissi"]'::jsonb, 'Mardala is a traditional percussion instrument (drum) of Odisha, essential to Odissi music and dance performances. It is played with hands.'),
(NULL, 'Which traditional Odia festival involves women applying alta (red dye) on their feet and enjoying swings?', 'Raja Parba', 'Nuakhai', 'Durga Puja', 'Kartika Purnima', 'A', 1, 'Culture & Traditions', 'easy', '["Raja Parba", "Alta", "Women Festival", "Traditions"]'::jsonb, 'During Raja Parba, women and girls apply alta (red dye) on their feet, wear new clothes, and enjoy swings, celebrating the fertility of Mother Earth.'),
